    • Method Detail

      • clearEnabledDomains

        public static void clearEnabledDomains()
        Call to clear out and essentially disable all domains. This is usually followed by calls to enable specific domains in a specific LIFO order.

      • addEnabledDomain

        public static void addEnabledDomain(java.lang.String domainname)
        Add (or move) a domain to the top of the enabledDomains list. Items added to the list should be considered LIFO. That is, each item added to the list is put at the top of the list.

      • removeEnabledDomain

        public static void removeEnabledDomain(java.lang.String domainname)
        Remove a domain from the enabledDomains list. Ignores invalid domains and domains not in the list.

      • getEnabledDomains

        public static java.lang.String[] getEnabledDomains()
        Returns a String array of the currently enabled domains in the order they should be processed. That is, item[0] is the first with highest precedence, etc..
        Returns:
        String[] of enabled domain names in the order they should be processed. Can return an array of 0-length.

      • getEnabledDomainsString

        public static java.lang.String getEnabledDomainsString()
        Returns:
        the array of enabled domains as a comma-separated list in a single String. If no domains are enabled then this should be an empty String.

      • isDomainSupported

        public static boolean isDomainSupported(java.lang.String domainname)

      • enableDomains

        public static void enableDomains(java.lang.String domains)
        Enable specified test domains and disable those not specified. We attempt to enable the domains in the order listed in domains.
        Parameters:
        domains - -- case-insensitive string of domains to enable. Examples:
        "Java": Enables Java domain and disables all others.
        "Java, HTML": Enables Java and Html domains--in that order--and disables all others.
        See Also:
        clearEnabledDomains(), addEnabledDomain(String)

        Parameters:
